WEBVTT

00:00:01.070 --> 00:00:11.820
Confused about high school? Then you should watch Nickelodeon's Welcome Freshman and we can make you confuse no more!

00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:13.820
Kevin, what are you doing?

00:00:13.820 --> 00:00:15.820
I'm taking a commercial for a show.

00:00:15.820 --> 00:00:16.820
How?

00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:18.820
What has been taken?

00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:22.820
Oh, then who's taking us now?

00:00:22.820 --> 00:00:26.220
I don't know.

00:00:26.220 --> 00:00:27.220
Whoa!

00:00:27.220 --> 00:00:31.220
Watch Welcome Freshman every Saturday at 5-4 Central on Nickelodeon!

00:00:31.220 --> 00:00:32.220
Kevin?

00:00:32.220 --> 00:00:33.220
Yeah?

00:00:33.220 --> 00:00:35.220
I'm confused.

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:39.220
My perfect 80s album? It's gotta make me dance.

00:00:39.220 --> 00:02:33.500
Has the right to remain silent, but explains it all Saturday at 8-7 Central on Snick!

00:02:33.500 --> 00:03:05.030
Can do something about it.

00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:11.720
He complained about the class budget, but nobody bothered to vote for a class treasurer.

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:18.190
He's dankotty who voted for himself, so he won.

00:03:18.190 --> 00:03:23.190
And he ended up spending the whole budget on uniforms for the Rocket Club.

00:03:23.190 --> 00:03:29.190
And people always hate to sleep dance decor, but no one ever stops Ninzy Dinsdale from taking over.

00:03:29.190 --> 00:03:37.330
Even though she always goes for that ever popular fuzzy unicorn theme.

00:03:37.330 --> 00:03:41.330
So okay, we all get episodic about stuff sometimes.

00:03:41.330 --> 00:03:46.330
But in the grand scheme of things, a goofy spring dance and a class budget don't add up to much.

00:03:46.330 --> 00:03:53.330
On the other hand, some things really do matter, and if you care enough, it's time to take action.

00:03:53.330 --> 00:04:52.920
Hey, Colerson.

00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:54.920
Sam, we've gotta do something about this.

00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:55.920
About what?

00:04:55.920 --> 00:04:58.920
Look at this article on Wilcott Industries.

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:00.920
You mean that huge company over on Piedon Road?

00:05:00.920 --> 00:05:01.920
That's the one.

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:03.920
So they're expanding their facilities, so what?

00:05:03.920 --> 00:05:05.920
Bottom paragraph, line two.

00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:08.920
Wow, I had no idea they did animal testing.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:09.920
Neither did I.

00:05:09.920 --> 00:05:12.920
And we've been getting their bubble baths since I was a little kid.

00:05:12.920 --> 00:05:15.920
And I've been using their shaving cream for as long as I've been shaving.

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:17.920
And that's like four months already.

00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:19.920
Makes me feel guilty about all those bubble baths.

00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:21.920
Yeah, it's a really big drag.

00:05:21.920 --> 00:05:22.920
But what can you do?

00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:24.920
Hey, you going to Kelly Ding Bingo's party this weekend?

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:26.920
Sam, wait a minute.

00:05:26.920 --> 00:05:30.920
We can't just sit back and let some business in our own neighborhood do something we're really against.

00:05:30.920 --> 00:05:32.920
Clarissa, Wilcott is a huge company.

00:05:32.920 --> 00:05:34.920
You can't just call them up and say,

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:36.920
please stop your animal testing.

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:38.920
And they go, sure, kid, whatever you say.

00:05:38.920 --> 00:05:41.920
But Sam, there's plenty of stuff we can do.

00:05:41.920 --> 00:05:45.920
Like we can get people to write letters, hand out pamphlets, boycott their products.

00:05:45.920 --> 00:05:47.920
Clarissa, that's not gonna do any good.

00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:49.920
Hey, and I can write about this in the Thomas Tupper time.

00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:52.920
Power of the press, First Amendment, freedom of speech.

00:05:52.920 --> 00:05:54.920
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:56.920
It's easy to talk about change in the world,

00:05:56.920 --> 00:05:58.920
but who's gonna listen to a couple of high school kids?

00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:00.920
Sam, I can't believe you're so cynical.

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:02.920
The whole point of the press is to be an advocate for change.

00:06:02.920 --> 00:06:05.920
I guess even Rush Limbaugh would agree with that.

00:06:05.920 --> 00:06:08.920
I'm gonna write the editorial of this century.

00:06:09.920 --> 00:06:12.920
Dear readers, what's the big bad secret on Pine Road?

00:06:12.920 --> 00:06:14.920
Here's the scoop.

00:06:14.920 --> 00:06:21.050
Hey, look, Sam.

00:06:21.050 --> 00:06:23.050
A letter from Wilcott Industries. We did it.

00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:26.050
Clarissa, your editorial on the Thomas Tupper times

00:06:26.050 --> 00:06:29.050
did generate like a gazillion names on our petition.

00:06:29.050 --> 00:06:30.050
I'm not surprised.

00:06:30.050 --> 00:06:32.050
Oh, right, Mr. Optimus.

00:06:32.050 --> 00:06:36.160
Yeah, yeah, yeah. So what's it say?

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:39.160
Dear Ms. Darling, thank you for your interest in Wilcott Industries.

00:06:39.160 --> 00:06:42.160
We always enjoy hearing from our many customers.

00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:44.160
As a token of our appreciation,

00:06:44.160 --> 00:06:47.160
here is a free sample of our new SuperGel move.

00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:51.160
Yours, Haberford B. Wilcott III, President.

00:06:51.160 --> 00:06:53.160
What does that have to do with animal testing?

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:57.160
Nothing, Sam, but I have a feeling that's the point.

00:06:57.160 --> 00:07:04.740
Hey, anybody see my ball? It was a, uh, Titleist VI.

00:07:04.740 --> 00:07:07.740
Ferguson, this is a house, not a golf course.

00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:10.740
I shanked my drive. What do you want from me?

00:07:10.740 --> 00:07:13.740
I didn't keep my head down. I think your ball went into the kitchen.

00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:16.740
Thanks. I think this might be a bogey hole for me.

00:07:16.740 --> 00:07:18.740
Ferguson, what is all this?

00:07:18.740 --> 00:07:24.920
Sis, what is the preferred sport of Fortune 500 executives?

00:07:24.920 --> 00:07:25.920
Need I say more?

00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:28.920
But do they dress like they're certifiably insane?

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:30.920
It's the retro look.

00:07:30.920 --> 00:07:33.920
I got the whole shebang from old man Gravabaca for a song.

00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:35.920
Nice, huh?

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:41.920
Okay, keep your head down. Keep your left arm straight.

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:43.920
Hey, you think this moose is any good?

00:07:43.920 --> 00:07:45.920
Sam, how can you even think about it?

00:07:45.920 --> 00:07:49.920
Clarissa, it doesn't look like Wilcott Industries is going to change their ways.

00:07:49.920 --> 00:07:51.920
I mean, they just shined you on.

00:07:51.920 --> 00:07:53.920
I'm not giving up that easily.

00:07:53.920 --> 00:07:55.920
This letter is totally insulting.

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:59.920
Did I really think we're so apathetic we can be placated by a form letter and a free sample?

00:07:59.920 --> 00:08:01.920
Hey, Spore. Hey, Sam.

00:08:01.920 --> 00:08:03.920
Hi, guys. How was the yard sale?

00:08:03.920 --> 00:08:05.920
Oh, it was great. Look what I got.

00:08:05.920 --> 00:08:08.900
That's familiar.

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:11.900
It's Mr. Gravabaca bought it at our yard sale just last year.

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:14.900
Well, I knew the second I sold it that I'd want it back someday.

00:08:14.900 --> 00:08:17.900
Woodstock, the ultimate musical sit-in.

00:08:17.900 --> 00:08:20.900
And now it's mine again.

00:08:20.900 --> 00:08:24.900
Uh-huh, until our next garage sale.

00:08:24.900 --> 00:08:29.900
Hey, Sam, I know a way we might get our message to Wilcott.

00:08:29.900 --> 00:08:30.900
What's that?

00:08:30.900 --> 00:08:34.900
Well, he may not care about a high school paper and a lot of kids' signatures,

00:08:34.900 --> 00:08:37.900
but I bet he'll care when we take our cars right to his doorstep.

00:08:37.900 --> 00:08:39.900
Why would he pay attention to us?

00:08:39.900 --> 00:08:41.900
Not just you and me, Sam.

00:08:41.900 --> 00:08:43.900
I'm talking about a whole bunch of us,

00:08:43.900 --> 00:08:47.900
with flyers and signs and loud voices, a broadcast sit-in.

00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:48.900
I can get into that.

00:08:48.900 --> 00:08:50.900
My parents used to do it all the time.

00:08:50.900 --> 00:08:53.900
It's the only way Wilcott won't be able to ignore us.

00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:55.900
That's a great idea.

00:08:55.900 --> 00:08:58.900
We can get everyone who signed the petition

00:08:58.900 --> 00:09:01.900
to storm the building, stage a coup,

00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:04.900
take over Wilcott's office and force his home.

00:09:04.900 --> 00:09:07.900
Well, I was thinking of something a little more peaceful,

00:09:07.900 --> 00:09:10.900
but I like the spirit, Sam. Let's hope it's contagious.

00:09:10.900 --> 00:09:17.230
Okay, we've plastered the area with flyers.

00:09:17.230 --> 00:09:19.230
We put a sign-up sheet at school

00:09:19.230 --> 00:09:22.230
and we've got a phone tree branching out of control.

00:09:22.230 --> 00:09:24.230
Tomorrow at this time, one full blast,

00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:26.230
full-scale protest will be in full swing.

00:09:26.230 --> 00:09:30.230
And that should mean one major blow to Wilcott and public apathy.

00:09:30.230 --> 00:09:33.230
Clarissa, what are you doing?

00:09:33.230 --> 00:09:35.230
Signing the powers of the beef, Ferguson,

00:09:35.230 --> 00:09:36.230
instead of sucking up to them.

00:09:36.230 --> 00:09:38.230
Something you wouldn't understand.

00:09:38.230 --> 00:09:40.230
Well, if you choose to behave like someone from another era,

00:09:40.230 --> 00:09:41.230
it's your life.

00:09:41.230 --> 00:09:44.230
But could you please do it somewhere else?

00:09:44.230 --> 00:09:46.230
This is the third tee.

00:09:46.230 --> 00:09:47.230
Third tee?

00:09:47.230 --> 00:09:49.230
On my new golf course.

00:09:49.230 --> 00:09:50.230
Your golf course?

00:09:50.230 --> 00:09:55.230
Darling Pines, a regulation championship 18-hole layup.

00:09:55.230 --> 00:09:58.230
See that little flag over there on the Soperstein's deck?

00:09:58.230 --> 00:10:03.940
That's the third tee.

00:10:03.940 --> 00:10:04.940
Slight breeze to the south.

00:10:04.940 --> 00:10:07.940
Think a seven-iron ought to do it.

00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:17.020
My backyard, too, you know.

00:10:17.020 --> 00:10:19.020
Quiet in the gallery, please.

00:10:19.020 --> 00:10:30.400
Slice.

00:10:30.400 --> 00:10:33.400
That'll cost me a stroke.

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:34.400
Cheerio.

00:10:34.400 --> 00:10:40.410
That's a good thing you didn't take a bar tree.

00:10:40.410 --> 00:10:43.660
Thanks, Warf. How's it going?

00:10:43.660 --> 00:10:44.660
Great.

00:10:44.660 --> 00:10:46.660
I'm just waiting for Sam to come over

00:10:46.660 --> 00:10:48.660
and finish up these signs, and then we're all set.

00:10:48.660 --> 00:10:50.660
Well, Clarissa, you know, we were rooting around the attic,

00:10:50.660 --> 00:10:52.660
and, uh, well, we found this.

00:10:52.660 --> 00:10:56.660
Now, this is my official protest jacket, 1968.

00:10:56.660 --> 00:10:58.660
Beautiful, isn't it?

00:10:58.660 --> 00:11:00.660
Yeah, well, it doesn't really fit me anymore.

00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:02.660
Oh, well, it's the jacket that's gotten smaller, right, Marshal?

00:11:02.660 --> 00:11:04.660
Yeah, well, you know, Jent, that attic's very dry.

00:11:04.660 --> 00:11:06.660
Things tend to shrink up there.

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:07.660
Okay.

00:11:07.660 --> 00:11:09.660
Sport here. I want you to have this.

00:11:09.660 --> 00:11:11.660
Thanks, Dad.

00:11:11.660 --> 00:11:13.660
Clarissa, we want to make sure that you're very careful

00:11:13.660 --> 00:11:14.660
at this protest field.

00:11:14.660 --> 00:11:15.660
Careful?

00:11:15.660 --> 00:11:17.660
Yeah, well, you know, Sport, these things have a way of

00:11:17.660 --> 00:11:18.660
getting out of hand.

00:11:18.660 --> 00:11:21.660
But, Dad, we're just planning a legal, peaceful demonstration.

00:11:21.660 --> 00:11:23.660
I mean, what's the worst that could happen?

00:11:23.660 --> 00:11:25.660
Burn, baby! Burn!

00:11:25.660 --> 00:11:27.660
Hell no! We won't go!

00:11:27.660 --> 00:11:32.660
El Pueblo, Unido, Hama, Sera, Unido!

00:11:32.660 --> 00:11:34.660
Hey, everybody, you ready for the protest?

00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:37.660
Hi, Sam. Nice gear. Where'd you get it?

00:11:37.660 --> 00:11:39.660
My uncle over at Dyer had a bit part

00:11:39.660 --> 00:11:41.660
