00:12:14.100 --> 00:12:17.100
Hey, Sam, we're just exercising our constitutional rights.

00:12:17.100 --> 00:12:20.100
I mean, come on. What's the worst that could happen?

00:12:20.100 --> 00:12:22.100
Okay.

00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:24.100
Now it's not the time to panic.

00:12:24.100 --> 00:12:27.100
One phone call and everything will be fine.

00:12:27.100 --> 00:12:29.100
I'm glad to hear that, Clarissa.

00:12:29.100 --> 00:12:33.100
Because around here, one phone call is all you're going to get.

00:12:33.100 --> 00:12:36.100
Um, Garb, can we have the phone now, please?

00:12:36.100 --> 00:12:44.680
Thanks.

00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:50.580
Well, go ahead. Call your dad.

00:12:50.580 --> 00:12:52.580
Me? You go ahead.

00:12:52.580 --> 00:12:54.580
Your parents are the protest kings.

00:12:54.580 --> 00:12:57.580
Your dad is so mellow in understanding.

00:12:57.580 --> 00:13:00.580
Clarissa, your parents are even more mellow in understanding.

00:13:00.580 --> 00:13:03.580
Much more. Besides, you have two of them. They call each other down.

00:13:03.580 --> 00:13:05.580
But, Sam, this is different. We're in jail.

00:13:05.580 --> 00:13:07.580
And I promise my parents nothing would happen.

00:13:07.580 --> 00:13:09.580
Your dad will be okay about it.

00:13:09.580 --> 00:13:11.580
About posting bail? Clarissa, I think in this case,

00:13:11.580 --> 00:13:13.580
